item.title: Acacia verniciflua (Bacchus Marsh variant)
item.dc:creator: david_francis
item.description: Acacia rostriformis (Bacchus Marsh Varnish Wattle) Shrub 1 - 6m tall generally multi-stemmed from the base Phyllodes narrowly elliptic to oblong elliptic 20 - 50mm long, 5 - 10mm wide, 2 longitudinal nerves (veins) per face Apex of phyllode excentrically mucronate, rostriform (beaked) Flower heads globular, 1-3 per axil Flowers around September

item.title: Turneromyia bassiana
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Great watching this - tapping with its tail at the covered entrance to the hole. Not sure if tapping was at its home or trying to encourage a spider out of its hole. Otherwise it was flying/patrolling low across the forest floor searching for spiders.
